{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"buffered"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A buffered channel can only be set unbuffered if the channel’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"internal buffers have been flushed. Newly created channels or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"channels which have returned "},{"code":"eof","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not require such a flush. For write-only channels, a call to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"g_io_channel_flush () is sufficient. For all other channels,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the buffers may be flushed by a call to g_io_channel_seek_position ().","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This includes the possibility of seeking with seek type ","type":"text"},{"code":"cur","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and an offset of zero. Note that this means that socket-based"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"channels cannot be set unbuffered once they have had data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"read from them."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On unbuffered channels, it is safe to mix read and write"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calls from the new and old APIs, if this is necessary for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"maintaining old code."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default state of the channel is buffered."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":". For any other encoding, the channel must be buffered."}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"set(buffered:)","externalID":"s:4GLib17IOChannelProtocolPAAE3set8bufferedySb_tF","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"buffered"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelprotocol\/set(buffered:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelProtocol"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelProtocol\/set(buffered:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop."}],"title":"MainContext","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannelProtocol/set(buffered:)":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelprotocol\/set(buffered:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For any other encoding, the channel must be buffered.","type":"text"}],"title":"set(buffered:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelProtocol\/set(buffered:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"buffered"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannelProtocol":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOChannelProtocol"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelprotocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOChannelProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOChannel"},{"type":"text","text":" data type aims to provide a portable method for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"using file descriptors, pipes, and sockets, and integrating them","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into the main event loop (see [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"]). Currently,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"full support is available on UNIX platforms; support for Windows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is only partially complete."}],"title":"IOChannelProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelProtocol","role":"symbol"}}}